name: The Big Game Barbeque Meat Chili
author: Anne Banks
summary: Not for the health conscious, but a huge hit with the men in my family while watching football on Sundays. Even better with onions and peppers, but this is the tried-and-true version. Enjoy!
ingredients: 1 (55 ounce) can baked beans (such as Bush's Homestyle®)
¼ cup barbeque sauce (such as Jack Daniel's®)
2 (13 ounce) packages kielbasa sausage, thinly sliced
directions: Stir baked beans, kidney beans, cannellini beans, barbeque sauce, and brown sugar together in a large bowl
Heat a large skillet over medium-high heat
Cook and stir beef, sweet Italian sausage, and hot Italian sausage in the hot skillet until browned and crumbly, 5 to 7 minutes; pour meat mixture into a slow cooker
Cook and stir kielbasa in the same skillet over medium-high heat until browned, 5 to 7 minutes; add to slow cooker
Pour bean mixture over meats in the slow cooker and stir to combine
Cook on Low for 10 to 12 hours
